# Project Bootstrap

At the start of every session, read these files in order:

1. **`CLAUDE.md`** — Repo identity, locked decisions, core rules, environment variables
2. **`docs/build-notes/quick-reference.md`** — Cheat sheet: current state, code patterns, common commands
3. **`docs/backlog-execution.md`** — Current work items and priorities

## Why This Matters
- CLAUDE.md contains locked technical decisions that MUST NOT be violated
- Quick-reference has the real code patterns and commands for this specific repo
- Backlog tells you what to work on next

## Rules
- Never start coding without reading CLAUDE.md first
- If CLAUDE.md and quick-reference.md conflict, CLAUDE.md wins
- If you're unsure about a convention, check these files before guessing
